Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper deals with text summarization, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the purview of cs.CL.
2. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper discusses the evaluation of summarization algorithms using ROUGE, which is a popular metric in the field of information retrieval. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a new model of summarization that integrates several dimensions of summarization, which could involve machine learning techniques. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper deals with a problem that is relevant to the broader field of AI, i.e., how to automatically summarize large amounts of text. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper compares different summarization algorithms and discusses their performance on a specific dataset, which could involve the use of data structures and algorithms.
